title: Trump breaks silence on Instagram to promote his NFTs - but critics say the art is 'cringey'
description: Donald Trump has released a second collection of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) as the 2024 presidential race heats up.

title: K-pop star Moonbin dies aged 25
description: Moonbin, a member of the K-pop band Astro, has died aged 25, according to a statement from the group's label.

title: 84-year-old white man pleads not guilty over shooting of black teen who knocked on wrong door
description: An 84-year-old white man accused of shooting a black teenager has pleaded not guilty in a US court.

title: Missing rugby player feared to have drowned
description: A British rugby player who went missing in Barcelona last year is feared to have drowned.

title: Russian ship 'spying' around wind farms off UK coast in possible sabotage plot
description: A Russian "spy" ship stopped at sites around wind farms off the Scottish coast in order to gather intelligence, an investigation has claimed.

title: Cat killing competition for children cancelled after backlash
description: A competition encouraging children to kill as many cats as possible has been cancelled following a backlash.

title: TikTok to crack down on climate change denial
description: TikTok is to start removing videos that deny the existence of climate change.

title: Alleged former Wagner commanders admit killing children in Ukraine
description: Two men, who claim to be former commanders in the Russian paramilitary mercenary group Wagner, have told an exiled human rights group they killed children and civilians in eastern Ukraine.

title: Baby blue-coloured spiral resembling a galaxy appears amid Northern Lights
description: Northern Lights enthusiasts were left "bewildered" after a baby blue-coloured spiral resembling a galaxy appeared amid the aroura in the skies of Alaska.

title: India to surpass China as the most populated country in world
description: India is on track to surpass China as the most populated country in the world, according to United Nations data.

title: Eight fishermen feared dead, as others survive without food or water, after tropical cyclone
description: Eight fishermen are feared to have drowned and another 11 have been rescued from an island off the Australian coast after they were caught in the path of a tropical cyclone.

title: At least 29 killed in Beijing hospital fire
description: A fire at a hospital in China has killed at least 29 people, authorities said.
